    {
      "id": "PopularPost250440",
      "post_content": "tavaritz, I hate to say it, but you don't know how banding works. Banding is only ever declared or invoked when forming a band to attack. Once combat begins, you can't disband your creatures -- they're stuck together until the end of combat. You certainly can't have a creature escape being blocked by having it abandon its partner(s).  \n  \nEven in the rare case of effects that actually remove the banding ability from a creature, I believe the creatures would still stay banded once the attack had begun.  \n  \nBanding really isn't complicated -- most people just assume it is or that you can do all sorts of things that you just plain can't.",
      "posted_by": "Stentorian",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost250440\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">tavaritz, I hate to say it, but you don't know how banding works. Banding is only ever declared or invoked when forming a band to attack. Once combat begins, you can't disband your creatures -- they're stuck together until the end of combat. You certainly can't have a creature escape being blocked by having it abandon its partner(s).<br/><br/>Even in the rare case of effects that actually remove the banding ability from a creature, I believe the creatures would still stay banded once the attack had begun.<br/><br/>Banding really isn't complicated -- most people just assume it is or that you can do all sorts of things that you just plain can't.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '250440'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy83662\">Stentorian</span>\r\n                                (6/9/2012 9:18:58 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_p